race_comments: Zane Smith has won the NextEra Energy 250 at Daytona International Speedway, his fourth career victory in the NASCAR Camping World Truck Series. Prior to the start of the race, the following vehicle(s) dropped to the rear of the field under penalty for the reason indicated: Nos. 56 (engine change), #30, 22 (Unapproved Adjustments), #75 (Missing Driver Intros).

Chandler Smith won the Victoria's Voice 200 presented by Westgate Resorts at Las Vegas Motor Speedway, his third career NASCAR Camping World Truck Series victory. Prior to the start of the race, the following trucks dropped to the rear of the field for the reasons indicated: No. 3 and 19 (unapproved adjustments) and No. 46 (Driver Change).

Corey Heim won the FR8 208 at Atlanta Motor Speedway, his first career NASCAR Camping World Truck Series victory. Prior to the start of the race, the following trucks dropped to the rear of the field for the reason indicated: No. 3, 4, 43, 61, and 66 (unapproved adjustments).

Zane Smith has won the XPEL 225 at the Circuit of The Americas, his fifth career victory in the NASCAR Camping World Truck Series. Prior to the start of the race, the following vehicle(s) dropped to the rear of the field under penalty for the reason(s) indicated: Nos. 20, 4, 44, 02, 88, 37, 45, 24, 9, 30, 43, 33, 46, 25 (Unapproved Adjustments).

William Byron has won the Blu-Emu Maximum Pain Relief 200 at Martinsville Speedway, his 8th career victory in the NASCAR Camping World Truck Series. Prior to the start of the race, the following vehicle(s) dropped to the rear of the field under penalty for the reason(s) indicated: Nos. 20 (Unapproved Adjustments).

Ben Rhodes has won the Pinty's Truck Race on Dirt at Bristol Motor Speedway Dirt, his sixth career victory in the NASCAR Camping World Truck Series. Prior to the start of the race, the following vehicle(s) dropped to the rear of the field under penalty for the reason(s) indicated: Nos. 1 (Backup truck), 49 (Unapproved Adjustments).

John Hunter Nemechek won the 3rd running of the Dead On Tools 200 at Darlington Raceway, his 12th victory in the NASCAR Camping World Truck Series Series. Prior to the start of the race, the following truck dropped to the rear of the field under penalty for the reasons indicated: No. 30 (unapproved adjustments).

Zane Smith won the Heart of America 200 at Kansas Speedway, his sixth NASCAR Camping World Truck Series victory. Prior to the start of the race the following trucks dropped to the rear of the field under penalty for the reason indicated: #30, #25 (unapproved adjustments), #52 (driver change).

Stewart Friesen has won the SpeedyCash.com  220 at Texas Motor Speedway, his third career victory in the NASCAR Camping World Truck Series. Prior to the start of the race, the following vehicle(s) dropped to the rear of the field under penalty: Nos. 4, 3, 22, 32, 23, 33 (Unapproved Adjustments), No. 91 (Backup Truck).

Ross Chastain won the North Carolina Education Lottery 200 at Charlotte Motor Speedway, his fourth career NASCAR Camping World Truck Series victory. Prior to the start of the race, the following trucks dropped to the rear of the field for the reasons indicated: No. 1 and 22 (unapproved adjustments).

Corey Heim won the Toyota 200 at World Wide Technology Raceway, his second NASCAR Camping World Truck Series victory. Prior to the start of the race the following trucks dropped to the rear of the field under penalty for the reason indicated: #1, #12, #33 (unapproved adjustments).

Kyle Busch has won the DoorDash 250 at Sonoma Raceway, his 62nd career victory in the NASCAR Camping World Truck Series . Prior to the start of the race, the following vehicle(s) dropped to the rear of the field under penalty: Nos. 42, 46 (unapproved adjustments).

Todd Gilliland won the Clean Harbors 150 at Knoxville Raceway, his 3rd NASCAR Camping World Truck Series victory. Prior to the start of the race the following cars dropped to the rear of the field under penalty for the reasons indicated: #12, 24 (missed driver intros).

Ryan Preece won the Rackley Roofing 200 at Nashville Superspeedway, his second career NASCAR Camping World Truck Series victory. Prior to the start of the race the following vehicle(s) dropped to the rear under the following penalty: No. 22 (unapproved adjustments), No. 15 (multiple inspection failures).

Parker Kligerman has won the O'Reilly Auto Parts 150 at Mid-Ohio Sports Car Course, his 3rd career victory in the NASCAR Camping World Truck Series Series. Prior to the start of the race, the following vehicle(s) dropped to the rear of the field under penalty for the reason(s) indicated: Nos. 44, 22, 19 – Unapproved adjustments

Chandler Smith has won the CRC Brakleen 150 at Pocono Raceway, his fourth career victory in the NASCAR Camping World Truck Series. Prior to the start of the race, the following vehicle(s) dropped to the rear of the field under penalty: No. 33 (Unapproved adjustments).

John Hunter Nemechek won the Kansas Lottery 200, his 13th career NASCAR Camping World Truck Series victory. Prior to the start of the race the following trucks dropped to the rear of the field for the reasons indicated: No. 22, 33, 43 and 46 (unapproved adjustments).

Matt Dibenedetto won the Chevy Silverado 250 at Talladega Superspeedway, his first NASCAR Camping World Truck Series victory. Prior to the start of the race the following truck dropped to the rear of the field under penalty for the reason indicated: #30 (unapproved adjustments).

Ty Majeski won the Baptist Health 200 at Homestead-Miami Speedway, his second career NASCAR Camping World Truck Series victory. Prior to the start of the race, the following trucks dropped to the rear of the field for the reason indicated: No. 17, 33 and 45 (unapproved adjustments).
